```

Create the file `bug-filter.xml` in the project&#39;s root directory. See the [Filter file documentation][1] (or [PDF version][2]) for details on the available options. Insert the following short snippet into the file to ignore EI and EI2 errors across all classes:

``` xml
&lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;UTF-8&quot;?&gt;
&lt;FindBugsFilter&gt;
  &lt;Match&gt;
    &lt;Or&gt;
      &lt;Bug code=&quot;EI, EI2&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;/Or&gt;
  &lt;/Match&gt;
&lt;/FindBugsFilter&gt;
```

The [Bug descriptions][3] page lists bug codes and patterns.

The `FindBugsFilter` root-level element name is a holdover.

---

As a side-note, too many accessors tend to indicate code isn&#39;t reaping the benefits of [object-oriented programming][4].


